genresAdvancedInfo.name: finnish tango
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Finnish tango is a unique style of tango that has been adapted to Finnish sensibilities. It is characterized by its slow, melancholic tempo and its emphasis on storytelling through music. Finnish tango often features lyrics that deal with themes of love, longing, and loss, and is a beloved genre that has been popular in Finland for over a century.
